HEADWORD: Toparchy
<hw>To"parch*y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Toparchies</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L. <ets>toparchia</ets>,
Gr. <?/. See <er>Toparch</er>.]</ety> <def>A small state, consisting of
a few cities or towns; a petty country governed by a toparch; <as>as,
Judea was formerly divided into ten <ex>toparchies</ex></as>.</def>
